==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: November
<hw>No*vem"ber</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>November</ets>, or <ets>Novembris</ets> (sc. <ets>mensis</ets>),
the ninth month of the old Roman year, which began with March, fr.
<ets>novem</ets> nine: cf. F. <ets>Novembre</ets>. See
<er>Nine</er>.]</ety> <def>The eleventh month of the year, containing
thirty days.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

